      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic isotropic material model for Ti-6Al-4V confirmed appropriate for sub-yield loading regime; frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw and rod validated against published literature.",
      "rationale": "Compression-bending test loads remain below yield for the screw body in the majority of constructs. Linear elastic constitutive model is well-established for titanium alloy implants under F1717 conditions. Contact friction coefficient sourced from peer-reviewed tribology literature and confirmed by sensitivity analysis showing < 3% QoI sensitivity to mu in range 0.15–0.25."
