      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production inventory tested across two independent laboratories. Lot traceability documented. Sample size provides 80% power to detect 10% mean difference at alpha=0.05 based on pre-study power calculation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions should span at least two load levels or two environmental conditions representative of the COU to achieve required level 3. Required level set at 3 given Model Risk Level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single standardized ASTM F1717 load configuration at room temperature only. No variation in load angle, displacement rate, or environmental condition was explored. This single-condition approach limits the ability to characterize model predictive capability across the broader COU envelope. Achieved level 2 reflects adequate characterization of the nominal condition but insufficient coverage of condition variability."
    },
