      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs selected (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the COU decision on construct mechanical performance adequacy.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are the primary outputs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly inform the regulatory decision on mechanical performance. Stiffness characterizes construct rigidity; yield force identifies onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm represents ultimate load-bearing capacity. All three are mechanistically linked to the clinical failure mode of interest."
